@OancaAndrei I just gave a look at your "todo list" for this PR, and I have a question - can we mark what we have now as "minimal usable" and start merging, and other boxes will be ticked by further PRs? I need to remind that it's not only a burden on you to implement stuff but also a burden on us to review it, so it's waaaaaaaaaaay better to have a thing come in several atomic PRs (each of them should ideally leave the product functional, even if not at the completely desired state) than in one giant PR that would be reviewed for weeks.

I must ask again, what is left on the server part to mark it as a first usable stage? IMHO the first usable stage is when syncplay is possible to be turned on/off globally by server admin and is joinable by anyone on the server. No groups types, no group pins, not even waiting is exactly needed. People can circumvent waiting by pausing manually (they're likely to be over some other communication channel to be able to ask to pause or pause themselves if it buffers).

So we can get this PR in, and _then_ build PRs that improve and polish the feature.

I run jellyfin on port 8096 and use a reverse proxy to access it from port 80/443. This feature was originally not working (GET `/socket` requests would 404) until I modified my reverse proxy settings. According to [this blog which helped me get it working](https://medium.com/@ibraheemabukaff/how-to-proxy-websockets-with-nginx-e333a5f0c0bb), websockets rely on some HTTP headers that are not forwarded through proxies by default.

Perhaps [the reverse proxy instructions](https://jellyfin.org/docs/general/networking/index.html) should be revised. The release notes should mention that websockets (which this relies on) may not work out of the box with an already working reverse proxy. 

I added the new `location /socket` part to my nginx config and now it works fine.
```
server {
  server_name MyServer.com;
  location /socket {
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
    proxy_pass "http://localhost:8096/socket";
  }
  location / {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:8096/;
  }
}
```

